  "original_title": "Sri Lanka\u2019s state-run Litro Gas to distribute cooking gas from July 06",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Sri Lanka\u2019s state-run Litro Gas to distribute cooking gas from July 06",
      "author": "Mahadiya Hamza",
      "body_lines": [
        "ECONOMYNEXT \u2013 Sri Lanka\u2019s state-run Litro Gas Lanka Ltd will distribute a mostly World Bank-funded liquid petroleum (LP) gas consignment from July 06, a spokesperson said.",
        "Previously, a government statement said an initial batch of 33,000 metric tons of LP gas bought at a cost of 20 million dollars will reach Sri Lanka by the first week of July.",
        "Litro procured 100,000 metric tons of LP gas \u2013 enough for four months \u2013 worth 90 million US dollars on June 30.",
        "The World Bank has funded 70 million dollars and the rest was funded by the state-run company.",
        "The consignment consists of 5 million 12.5kg cylinders, 1 million 5kg cylinders and 1 million 2.5kg cylinders and 70 percent of will be distributed for domestic use.",
        "The remaining 30 percent will be distributed for commercial use. (Colombo/Jul01/2022)"
      ],
